<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1916,2015]" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1916,1942]" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Hooks of male ninth abdominal tergite close-set to each other, immobile, apices directing downwards. Female seventh abdominal tergite with transverse fold covering unpaired depression; subgenital plate not fused with the preceding sternite, with 1 pair of tubercles.
</paragraph>
